The paper deals with the problem of vision-based grasping, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The approach presented in the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for accurate grasping, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also presents a novel unsupervised learning algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve the use of robots, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
